Package liftProblemCode

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    TestRunner.IFunc  
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    FloorsWaitingSets
    This class holds lists of floors waiting to go up or down as 2 separate lists.
    Lift
    This is an entity that stores the state of the lift - we store things like
    the current floor
    the direction it is moving in
    the lift number - a simple character lift identifier
    the list of queued floors for the lift
    the next positioning floor for the lift
    LiftCaller
    This threaded class reflects the use case of users calling the lift.
    LiftChooser
    This class selects a suitable Lift and schedules it to stop.
    LiftProgramRunner
    This is the main class - its role is to kick off 3 sets of threads - one for the floors waiting another set for the various lifts, along with their identifiers a lift chooser that looks at the state of play and allocates lifts.
    LiftThread
    This thread emulates the behaviour of the lift itself as it travels around and users press buttons on floors.
    SingletonPropertyReader  
    TestRunner
